    <help format="markdown"><![CDATA[
This tool fetches information from OpenAlex for works, authors, and institutions. OpenAlex is a scholarly metadata index covering publications, authors, institutions, citations, references, topics, and Open Access locations.

**Input entities**

- **Works**: use OpenAlex work IDs, DOIs, DOI URLs, OpenAlex work URLs, or titles.
  Examples: `W4398182689`, `10.1093/nar/gkae410`, `https://doi.org/10.1093/nar/gkae410`.
- **Authors**: use OpenAlex author IDs, OpenAlex author URLs, ORCIDs, ORCID URLs, or author names.
  Examples: `A5023888391`, `0000-0001-6187-6610`, `https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6187-6610`.
- **Institutions**: use ROR IDs, ROR URLs, OpenAlex institution IDs, OpenAlex institution URLs, or institution names.
  Examples: `https://ror.org/0245cg223`, `0245cg223`, `I161046081`, `University of Freiburg`.

**ROR identifiers**

ROR, the Research Organization Registry, provides persistent identifiers for research organizations such as universities, institutes, hospitals, and funders. OpenAlex links institutions to ROR where possible, which makes ROR useful for institution-level publication searches.

For example, the University of Freiburg has ROR `https://ror.org/0245cg223` and OpenAlex institution ID `I161046081`. To retrieve University of Freiburg publications, choose **Institutions** as the input entity, enter `https://ror.org/0245cg223`, and select **Institution works**.

**Input format**

- Pasted input accepts one identifier, title, author, or institution per line.
- Dataset input accepts text or tabular data and always reads the first column from each non-comment row.
- Name and title inputs are resolved to the top OpenAlex search result.

**Modes**

- **Summary**: basic metadata for resolved work inputs.
- **Citing papers**: papers that cite resolved work inputs.
- **References**: bibliography entries for resolved work inputs.
- **Related works**: works related to resolved work inputs.
- **Authors**: author details for resolved work inputs.
- **Concepts**: research topics/concepts for resolved work inputs.
- **Download PDFs**: download available Open Access PDFs for resolved work inputs, or for fetched author/institution works when combined with those modes.
- **Author works**: publications for resolved author inputs.
- **Institution works**: publications for resolved institution inputs, including ROR-based university queries.

**Options**

- Work-list outputs can be filtered by Open Access status, publication year range, and OpenAlex work type.
- Work-list outputs can be sorted by citation count or publication year.
- XPAC expansion can be enabled for broader OpenAlex coverage. XPAC expands the OpenAlex works index but may include lower-confidence metadata.
- A polite-pool email address can be supplied for improved API access.

**Example use cases**

- **Get all DOIs from the University of Freiburg**: choose **Institutions**, enter `https://ror.org/0245cg223`, select **Institution works**, set **Max works to fetch** to `All`, and use the `DOI` column from the institution works output. OpenAlex returns works that it can link to the institution through affiliation metadata and ROR linkage.
- **Get University of Freiburg publications from 2020 through 2025**: choose **Institutions**, enter `https://ror.org/0245cg223`, select **Institution works**, set **Publication year from** to `2020`, and set **Publication year to** to `2025`.
- **Download available Open Access PDFs for an institution sample**: choose **Institutions**, enter `https://ror.org/0245cg223`, select **Institution works** and **Download available OA PDFs**, and set a small **Max works to fetch** value such as `3` or `10`. The PDF collection contains only works with direct downloadable Open Access PDF URLs.
- **Find papers by one author**: choose **Authors**, enter an ORCID such as `0000-0001-6187-6610` or an author name such as `Björn Grüning`, and select **Author works**. Name searches use the top OpenAlex author search result, so ORCID or OpenAlex author ID is preferred when available.
- **Inspect a known paper and its neighborhood**: choose **Works**, enter a DOI such as `10.1093/nar/gkae410`, and select **Summary**, **References**, **Citing papers**, **Related works**, **Authors**, and **Concepts**.
- **Batch mixed work identifiers**: choose **Works**, paste one DOI or OpenAlex work ID per line, or upload a tabular dataset. For datasets, only the first column is read.

**Outputs**

Tabular outputs include the original input, resolved entity ID, resolved entity name, and mode-specific result columns. Galaxy metadata column names are set for every tabular output. PDF outputs are returned as a dataset collection and include only records with direct downloadable Open Access PDF URLs.
    ]]></help>
